There are four types of users for this real-estate web application:            
Homebuyer
User Story Description  
1) As a homebuyer, I want to create an account so I can save my progress.
- User presses “Login” button on the top right corner
- User must enter username and password and click login button
    a. If they do not have an account, they must create an account using the “create account” button at the top of the login page
    b. Then they must fill out the form with their name, email address and password.
Acceptance Criteria
- User must be able to create an account
- User must be able to delete their account
- User can edit their account details

2) As a homebuyer, I want to search for properties for sale with specific criteria.
- User clicks on the "filter" button on the top right
- User will get different filtering options to select from based on their requirements:
- Location: The user can choose the country, and/or the city of their choice  
- Price range: The user can specify the minimum and/or the maximum amount to pay for the property
- Amenities: The user can choose between a furnished and a non-furnished house
- Size: The user can give a range of the desired area of the house in sqm2
- Rooms: The user can specify the number of bedrooms and/or bathrooms. 


3) As a homebuyer, I want to be able to save appealing properties in a separate list for easy access.  
- The user presses the “heart” icon below the property’s image. This property will then be saved in the “favourites” list. 
-The “favourites” list is accessible by clicking the “favourites” button next to the “account” button on the top right of the webpage


4) As a homebuyer, I want to be able to visit a property of interest. 
- The user clicks on the “show more” button or on the image of the house.
- A new page will open, showing all details related to the property, with an option to request a visit. 
- After selecting this feature, a small calendar of availabilities will open for the user to choose a date and time for the visit.  

5) As a homebuyer, I might need some help with property selection from a broke, to seal the deal. 
- The user clicks on “Choose a Broker”, and gets associated with an available broker within the same city. 
- The user will receive the broker’s contact information (the conversation between them should be made outside the web app). 

6) As a homebuyer, I want to know the expected monthly payments based on a loan and the interest rate. 
- The user clicks on the “mortgage calculator” button 
- A form will open, asking for the yearly interest rate, the loan amount, and the duration of the loan. 
- After submitting the form, the user will get an estimate of the expected monthly payments. 


Property Renters
User Story Description
As a property renter, I want to create an account so that I can save my progress.
1. User presses “Log in” button on the top right corner
2. User must enter username and password and click login button
    a. If they do not have an account, they must create an account using the “create account” button at the top of the login page
    b. Then they must fill out the form with their name, email address and password.
Acceptance Criteria
- User must be able to create an account
- User must be able to delete their account
- User can edit their account details.

As a property rental, I want to search for properties to rent with my specific criteria.
1.	User clicks on the filter button on the top right.
2.	User will get different filtering options to select from based on their requirements:
    •	Location: the user can choose the country and/or a city
    •	Price range: the user can specify the minimum and/or the maximum amount to pay for the property.
    •	Amenities: the user can choose between a furnished and a non-furnished house.
    •	Size: the user can give a range of the desired area of the house in sqm2.
    •	Rooms: the user can specify the number of bedrooms and/or bathrooms.

As a property rental, I would like to be able to save appealing properties in a separate list for easy access.
1.	The user presses the “heart” icon below the property’s image. This property will then be saved in the favorites list.
2.	The favorites list is accessible by clicking the “favorites” button on the top right of the web page.

As a property rental, I want to be able to visit a property of interest.
1.	The user clicks on the “show more” button or on the image of the house.
2.	A new page will load showing all details related to the property with an option to request a visit.
3.	After selecting this feature, a small calendar of availabilities will open for the user to choose a date and time for the visit.

As a property rental, I might need some help with proper selection from a broker to seal deal.
1.	The user clicks on “Choose a broker” and gets associated with an available broker within the same city.
2.	The user will receive the broker’s contact information (the conversation between them should be made outside the web app).

Broker 
User Story Description
As a broker, I want to create an account so that I can save my progress. 
1.  User presses “Log in” button on the top right corner
2.  User must enter username and password and click login button
    a. If they do not have an account, they must create an account using the “create account” button at the top of the login page
    b. Then they must fill out the form with their name, email address and password. 
Acceptance Criteria
- User must be able to create an account
- User must be able to delete their account
- User can edit their account details

As a broker, I want to submit offers for buying properties on behalf  of my clients, and track the status of their offers.
1.  User clicks on the desired property.
2.  The property will open the house in a new page with the details of the house
3.  User can then click on “Submit Offer”
4.  User fills the offer form 
    a. User enters the name of the broker
    b. User enters client information
    c. User enters offer
5.  User submits the form
6.  User gets a confirmation that the offer was submitted successfully
7.  The property gets added to the “My Account” tab on the navigation bar
Acceptance Criteria
- User must be able to submit offers
- Must be able to view the status of the offer
- Must validate the entered information (ex: price can’t be negative)
- Must receive confirmation

As a broker, I want to request a visit to a property on behalf of my clients in order to show them properties that interest them
1.  User clicks on the house he wants to book a visit for
2.  User clicks on “book a visit” button 
    a. select a time slot
    b. Enter the name of the broker
    c. Enter the name of the client
3.  User clicks Submit 
Acceptance Criteria
- Appointment slots should update availabilities
- User must be able to edit their appointment
- User must be able to update client with booking information

As a broker, I want to perform CRUD operations on property listing to update the listings
1.  User clicks on the “Properties” tab on the navigation bar
2.  User can browse all the properties he owns
3.  The properties will be visible as a series of boxes that contain an image of the property, the price, and the city. 
    a. User can click on a property to get more information
    b. User can then click on the “edit” button to update the details of the listing or to delete a listing
4.  User can create a new property by clicking the “Create” button
    a. The user has to upload a picture of the house
    b. User had to upload all the details asked. 
Acceptance Criteria
- Property listings should be updated on home page
- If a listing is deleted the homebuyer must be notified 

